types.name: __Schema
types.description: A GraphQL Schema defines the capabilities of a GraphQL server. It exposes all available types and directives on the server, as well as the entry points for query, mutation, and subscription operations.

fields.name: types
fields.description: A list of all types supported by this server.

fields.name: queryType
fields.description: The type that query operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: mutationType
fields.description: If this server supports mutation, the type that mutation operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: subscriptionType
fields.description: If this server support subscription, the type that subscription operations will be rooted at.

fields.name: directives
fields.description: A list of all directives supported by this server.

types.name: String
types.description: The `String` scalar type represents textual data, represented as UTF-8 character sequences. The String type is most often used by GraphQL to represent free-form human-readable text.

types.name: __Type
types.description:
The fundamental unit of any GraphQL Schema is the type. There are many kinds of types in GraphQL as represented by the `__TypeKind` enum.

Depending on the kind of a type, certain fields describe information about that type. Scalar types provide no information beyond a name and description, while Enum types provide their values. Object and Interface types provide the fields they describe. Abstract types, Union and Interface, provide the Object types possible at runtime. List and NonNull types compose other types.

types.name: __TypeKind
types.description: An enum describing what kind of type a given `__Type` is.

enumValues.name: SCALAR
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a scalar.

enumValues.name: OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an object. `fields` and `interfaces` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: INTERFACE
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an interface. `fields`, `interfaces`, and `possibleTypes` are valid fields.

enumValues.name: UNION
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a union. `possibleTypes` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: ENUM
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an enum. `enumValues` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: INPUT_OBJECT
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is an input object. `inputFields` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: LIST
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a list. `ofType` is a valid field.

enumValues.name: NON_NULL
enumValues.description: Indicates this type is a non-null. `ofType` is a valid field.

types.name: __Field
types.description: Object and Interface types are described by a list of Fields, each of which has a name, potentially a list of arguments, and a return type.

types.name: __InputValue
types.description: Arguments provided to Fields or Directives and the input fields of an InputObject are represented as Input Values which describe their type and optionally a default value.

fields.name: defaultValue
fields.description: A GraphQL-formatted string representing the default value for this input value.

types.name: Boolean
types.description: The `Boolean` scalar type represents `true` or `false`.

types.name: __EnumValue
types.description: One possible value for a given Enum. Enum values are unique values, not a placeholder for a string or numeric value. However an Enum value is returned in a JSON response as a string.

types.name: __Directive
types.description:
A Directive provides a way to describe alternate runtime execution and type validation behavior in a GraphQL document.

In some cases, you need to provide options to alter GraphQL's execution behavior in ways field arguments will not suffice, such as conditionally including or skipping a field. Directives provide this by describing additional information to the executor.

types.name: __DirectiveLocation
types.description: A Directive can be adjacent to many parts of the GraphQL language, a __DirectiveLocation describes one such possible adjacencies.

types.description: Commission Type (Possible values include Securities or Commodities)

types.name: ExchangeAccess
types.description: An ACES account exchange access.

types.name: AssetClass
types.description: An ACES asset class, aka financial instrument type.

types.name: TradingLimits
types.description: Various limits for the llimit tracking mechanism.

types.name: OrderValueLimits
types.description: Per day order value limits.

types.name: EFPQuantityLimits
types.description: EFP order quantity limits.

types.name: OrderQuantityLimit
types.description: Per asset class order quantity limit.

types.name: DayQuantityLimit
types.description: Per asset class day quantity limit.

types.name: AdvisorWrapFeesType
types.description: This is for BillingConfiguration and indicates whether other fees will be charged to the advisor account

types.name: AutomatedWrapFeeDetailsType
types.description: This is the optional monthly invoice percentage cap. When provided, it limits the advisor quarterly invoice to a certain percentage of the client's Net Asset Value. Mutualy exclusive with PercentOfNLVCap. When used in combination with type.INVOICE_LIMIT_Q it implies both a percentage and absolute amount cap (whichever is reached first).

types.name: AnnualBlendedPercentage
types.description: Annualize Blended Percentage

types.name: HighWaterMarkType
types.description: HighWaterMark Setup.

types.name: HighWaterMarkConfigurationType
types.description: HighWaterMark Configuration.

types.name: PreviousLossesType
types.description: Previous Losses for HighWaterMark.

types.name: CommissionScheduleType
types.description: Schedule of commission markups.

types.name: CommissionMarkupType
types.description: Specific markup in a commission schedule.

types.name: MarkupStaircaseType
types.description: A break in the markup staircase of a commission schedule.

types.name: InterestMarkupScheduleType
types.description: Schedule of interest rate markups.

types.name: InterestMarkupType
types.description: Interest Rate markups for a specific currency.

types.name: ExtPositionsTransfers
types.description: Details for transferring positions from a third party broker to IB using a specific transfer mechanism such as ACATS or ATON for one or more customer accounts at IB.

types.name: FeesTemplateBasedType
types.description: Fees template name previously created on Account Management.

types.name: ExtPositionsTransferType
types.description: Is used to indicate whether mutual funds are OK to be excluded from ACATS transfer.

types.name: PartialStockPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of stock positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialStockPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of a stock position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: PartialBondPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of bond positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialBondPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of a bond position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: PartialOptionPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of option positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialOptionPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of an option position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: PartialWarrantPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of warrant positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialWarrantPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of a warrant position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: PartialFundPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of fund positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialFundPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of a fund position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: PartialCashPositions
types.description: All information required to complete partial transfer of cash positions held in external accounts over to IB.

types.name: PartialCashPosition
types.description: Information required to complete partial transfer of a cash position held in external account over to IB.

types.name: DepositNotificationType
types.description: Customer Account at IB for which this Deposit Notification is being set. Only relevant for notifications sent as part of Account Management Requests for open IB accounts.

types.name: CheckDetailsType
types.description: Account Number of the customer at the Bank on which the check is drawn as noted on the check.

types.name: WireDetailsType
types.description: Reference Number or Payment ID of the Wire Transfer provided by the Bank.

types.name: ACHDetailsType
types.description: Name of the Bank from which the ACH transfer will originate.

types.name: IRADepositDetailsType
types.description: Type of the source IRA account, only required for rollover deposits. Rollover deposits currently restricted to be from Traditional, Roth and SEP IRA accounts only. Inherited IRA accounts may not be the source of a rollover deposit notification.

types.name: RecurringTransactionType
types.description: Customer Account at IB for which this recurring transaction is being set. Only relevant for instructions sent as part of Account Management Requests for open IB accounts.

types.name: ACHInstructionType
types.description: Account Number of the customer at the Bank.

types.name: IRAWithdrawalDetailsType
types.description: The tax rate for state withholding from the withdrawal. If not specified, implies customer indicates no withholding.

types.name: CustodianType
types.description: One individual or a legal entity that is the custodian for a UGMA / UTMA. Legal entities must detail one employee to be the signatory.

directives.name: skip
directives.description: Directs the executor to skip this field or fragment when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: include
directives.description: Directs the executor to include this field or fragment only when the `if` argument is true.

directives.name: deprecated
directives.description: Marks an element of a GraphQL schema as no longer supported.

args.name: reason
args.description: Explains why this element was deprecated, usually also including a suggestion for how to access supported similar data. Formatted using the Markdown syntax, as specified by [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org/).
